# .worktreeinclude — files to copy from main worktree when creating new worktrees
#
# List glob patterns (one per line) for gitignored files that should be copied
# to new worktrees. These are typically generated config files that aren't
# tracked in git but are needed for the dev environment to work.
#
# Lines starting with # are comments. Empty lines are ignored.
# Patterns are expanded using bash globbing relative to the repo root.
# Note: ** (recursive glob) requires bash 4.0+. macOS ships bash 3.2 by default;
# install bash 5 via Homebrew if you need ** patterns.

# Per-worktree local compose overrides (personal volume mounts, build overrides, etc.)
.worktree/docker-compose.local.yml
.fdsx/workflows/**/*
.fdsx/config.yaml

# If you use a personal Dockerfile, uncomment the next line or add it to .worktreeinclude.local:
# .worktree/personal/*/Dockerfile
